                      },
                      "date": 1972
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAYAL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at 65 MeV Yale",
                "University Electron Linear Accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two set of samples containing deuterium were used.",
                " 1. Deuterated polyethylene (C-2H2), one with diameter",
                "    of 12.7 cm and thickness of 2.06 cm, the second",
                "    with diameter 7.18 cm and thickness of 4.57 mm.",
                " 2. Heavy water (2H2-O) in a a thin plastic cylindrical",
                "    bottle with 7.62 cm diameter and 12.70 cm high.",
                "For background measurement, targets with light water",
                "and standard polyethylene with identical dimensions",
                "as deuterated targets were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Solenoid with length of 1.2m, inside",
                "diameter of 7.5 cm and maximal field of 5000 Oersted",
                "was used for neutron spin precession. After a flight",
                "path of 26m, photoneutrons were scattered from",
                "a polarization analyser (liquid helium or graphite)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four Pilot B plastic scintillators each",
                "coupled to 12.7 cm diam phototubes are used as",
                "neutron detectors to observe left-right asymmetries",
                "of neutrons scattered from the helium polarization",
                "analyser. Most of the data are obtained using two",
                "pilot-B plastic scintillators (12.70 cm diam x 15.24 cm",
                "thick) each coupled to an RCA 7046 photo-multiplier",
                "tube placed in the reaction plane at lab angles of",
                "+-130 deg and at a distance of 27.6 cm from the centre",
                "of the helium analyser. Other two neutron detectors",
                "12.70 cm diam x 7.62 cm thick with pilot-B plastic",
                "scintillators each coupled to an Amperex 58 AVP",
                "photomultiplier tube were used either in an up-down",
                "geometry or in a left-right geometry at lab angles",
                "of +-70deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LRASY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The polarization of the photo-neutrons is",
                "determined by observing the asymmetry in their",
                "scattering from a liquid-helium cryostat or a",
                "graphite cylinder placed at the end of a 25 m flight",
                "path."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Photoneutron energy was determined by time-of-",
                "flight over flight path of 26 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "BRST"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Electrons with energy of 65 MeV striked a 250",
                "mu-m thick tungsten foil and produce bremsstrahlung",
                "photons with a maximum energy of 65 MeV. The",
                "electrons which pass through the foil were absorbed",
                "in a 10.80 cm thick x 6.35 cm diam electrically",
                "insulated aluminium cylinder. Maximum beam current",
                "was 2 A with pulse duration of 10 ns and repetition",
                "rate of 330 Hz."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Polarisation was determined from left-right asymetry",
                "after subtraction of background contribution determined",
                "in measurement with light water and non-deuterated",
                "polyethylene"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " No information given. Given uncertainties",
                " are most probably statistical uncertainties"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrected for target scattering effects, correction",
                "amounts to 10% at 15 MeV neutron energy and to 20%",
                "at the lowest energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
